00:21:06,791 --> 00:21:09,250
I'm sure he was
just excited, Kodaka.

514
00:21:09,333 --> 00:21:10,416
How funny.

515
00:21:10,500 --> 00:21:13,458
So Pegasus was
jumping to conclusions.

516
00:21:13,541 --> 00:21:14,125
Huh?

517
00:21:14,208 --> 00:21:15,291
What did you say?

518
00:21:15,375 --> 00:21:16,708
I don't know what
you're talking about.

519
00:21:16,791 --> 00:21:19,041
Okay, let's move on
to something else.

520
00:21:19,125 --> 00:21:21,291
I heard you guys are
making a movie, huh?

521
00:21:21,375 --> 00:21:22,291
Uh huh.

522
00:21:22,375 --> 00:21:23,625
What kind of movie
is it anyway?

523
00:21:23,708 --> 00:21:25,166
I couldn't make heads
or tails outta what Maria

524
00:21:25,250 --> 00:21:26,583
was trying to explain to me.

525
00:21:26,666 --> 00:21:27,416
Yeah.

526
00:21:27,500 --> 00:21:29,000
Yeah, I can believe that.

527
00:21:30,583 --> 00:21:32,041
[KATE]
Oh, I see.

528
00:21:32,125 --> 00:21:34,958
So it's a coming of age story
based on a transfer student.

529
00:21:35,041 --> 00:21:36,791
The more you tell me about
it, the more it reminds me

530
00:21:36,875 --> 00:21:38,750
of that film,
"Boys Over the Slope".

531
00:21:38,833 --> 00:21:39,833
Really?

532
00:21:39,916 --> 00:21:40,583
I've never even
heard of that before.

533
00:21:40,666 --> 00:21:42,083
Yep.

534
00:21:42,166 --> 00:21:43,708
It's another coming of age
movie that most people consider

535
00:21:43,791 --> 00:21:44,875
a cult classic.

536
00:21:44,958 --> 00:21:45,750
It's good.

537
00:21:45,833 --> 00:21:47,250
I'm surprised you don't know it.

538
00:21:47,333 --> 00:21:49,416
You should watch it
for research, at least.

539
00:21:49,500 --> 00:21:50,500
Cool.

540
00:21:50,583 --> 00:21:52,708
That sounds like
good reference material.

541
00:21:52,791 --> 00:21:54,250
Great idea, Kate.

542
00:22:07,833 --> 00:22:08,250
[BOY IN FILM]
Wait.

543
00:22:08,333 --> 00:22:09,208
Big brother!

544
00:22:09,291 --> 00:22:09,958
Hey, Kotaro.

545
00:22:10,041 --> 00:22:10,833
What is it?

546
00:22:10,916 --> 00:22:12,333
It's Hiro-nii, he--

547
00:22:12,416 --> 00:22:15,541
He's in trouble, and
you've gotta help him!

548
00:22:15,625 --> 00:22:16,958
[KODAKA]
No way.

549
00:22:17,041 --> 00:22:18,166
Yozora.

550
00:22:18,250 --> 00:22:19,625
How could she?

551
00:22:19,708 --> 00:22:22,208
Why would she do
something like this?

552
00:22:22,291 --> 00:22:25,041
She plagiarized
the entire script!

553
00:23:57,250 --> 00:23:58,250
Okay, listen up.

554
00:23:58,333 --> 00:24:00,041
I'll explain
exactly what happened.

555
00:24:00,125 --> 00:24:02,416
I thought Sena and Kodaka were
dating, but that apparently

556
00:24:02,500 --> 00:24:04,083
was not the case at all.

557
00:24:04,166 --> 00:24:05,875
It may be hard
to accept as truth.

558
00:24:05,958 --> 00:24:07,833
I know; I can barely
believe it myself.

559
00:24:07,916 --> 00:24:10,083
No need to get upset;
let's stay calm.

560
00:24:10,166 --> 00:24:12,000
You seem almost
happy about it, Kate.

561
00:24:12,083 --> 00:24:12,833
No, no.

562
00:24:12,916 --> 00:24:14,666
I'm not happy in the least!

563
00:24:14,750 --> 00:24:16,083
Next time.

564
00:24:16,166 --> 00:24:18,916
The Sad-Case King and
the Stone-Cold Story.

565
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:21,083
That Kodaka's got it rough, huh?

566
00:24:21,166 --> 00:24:23,125
Maybe I have
a chance with him now.

